The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Software solutions provider CMC Ltd has posted a 47.95 per cent increase in profit after tax (PAT) at Rs 22.12 crore for the quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 14.95 crore in the same quarter last year. Total income of the company decreased 6.65 per cent to Rs 216.89 crore for the quarter from Rs 232.35 crore a year ago, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. The group recorded a profit after tax of Rs 23.41 crore for the period against Rs 16.15 crore for the corresponding quarter in the previous year.

 Bajaj Allianz Life Insurance has registered a profit of Rs 30 crore in the first quarter of this fiscal. It issued 536,703 policies in the quarter and received business premium of Rs 729 crore.

 Suave Hotels Ltd has recorded a net profit of Rs 1.01 crore in the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 34.93 lakh in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal. Total income for the quarter stood at Rs Rs 4.02 crore compared with Rs 1.99 crore in the year-ago period.

 Spice Mobiles has partnered Hutch to provide a bundling offer in the state. Under the offer, consumers of Spice S-410 and S-535 will get a Hutch prepaid connection with a one-year validity and 1,200 minutes of local calls.

 Samsung India has launched the 19 Bordeaux LCD television priced at Rs 21,000.

